article.headline: Southern U. 62, Alabama A&M 60
article.story: BATON ROUGE, La. (AP) -- Chris Davis scored 16 points as Southern University edged past Alabama A&M 62-60 in a Southwestern Athletic Conference game on Monday night. Chike Ekweozer added 14 points and 17 rebounds, while Geri Guillory had 12 for the Jaguars (7-20, 6-9), which led 35-31 at the half. Trant Simpson had 23 to lead Alabama A&M (8-18, 2-12), while Cornelius Hester added 14. Mickell Gladness contributed eight points and had 12 rebounds to lead A&M on the boards.
